[[File:Urium remains detail.png|left|150px]]
'''Urium remains''' are an item found and used in the [[Shades of Mort'ton (minigame)|Shades of Mort'ton]] [[minigame]]. To obtain these remains, the player must kill an [[Urium Shade]], located behind the gold door in the [[Shade Catacombs]].

To burn the Urium remains, first place [[redwood pyre logs]] on a funeral pyre, followed by the Urium remains, then ignite the pyre with a [[tinderbox]]. This will grant the player 500 [[Firemaking]] experience (750 with [[Morytania Diary|Morytania Diary 4]] complete), and 120.5 [[Prayer]] (180.7 with [[Morytania Diary|Morytania Diary 3]] complete) experience.

Urium remains will always reward the player with a gold [[shade key]], or some [[coins]]. Gold keys give unrestricted access to all areas of the shade tombs and opens the gold chests in the Urium area of the tombs, which give the best rewards out of all the chests.

Completing the [[Morytania Diary]] 3 offers 50% more [[Prayer]] experience, and completing the [[Morytania Diary]] 4 offers 50% more [[Firemaking]] experience. The Pyromancer's/Zealot's outfit does not increase Firemaking/Prayer experience gained from burning shade remains.

